{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.targetExponent\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">Format</span>.<span class=\"name\">targetExponent</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">totalExponent</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Suppose we have written a number where `totalExponent` is the position of the\nmost significant digit, where the unit digit corresponds to `1`. So, for example,\n`1.0b` has total exponent `1`, `0.1b` has total exponent `0`, `0.01b` has total\nexponent `-1`, and so on. This function computes which exponent that number\nshould have according to the given `Format`. So, for example, for the number\n`0.1b` in `binary64` format, it wants us to use the exponent `-53`, corresponding\nto the representation `2^52 * 2^(-53)`, which has a 53-bit mantissa. If the total\nexponent gets quite small, then the result exponent eventually gets capped at\n`spec.minExponent`, which first forces the result to be a subnormal number and\nthen, if the total exponent is even smaller, to be zero.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.targetExponent","kind":"def","line":72,"name":"Float.Model.Format.targetExponent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.lean#L72-L85"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.minExponent\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">Format</span>.<span class=\"name\">minExponent</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The smallest exponent possible for a number using the given specification,\nincluding subnormals.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.minExponent","kind":"def","line":65,"name":"Float.Model.Format.minExponent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.lean#L65-L70"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.exponentBias\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">Format</span>.<span class=\"name\">exponentBias</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The exponent bias. In packed formats, we store the sum of the true exponent and\nthe bias.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.exponentBias","kind":"def","line":58,"name":"Float.Model.Format.exponentBias","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.lean#L58-L63"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.mantissaBits\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">Format</span>.<span class=\"name\">mantissaBits</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The number of bits in the mantissa, *including the implicit bit*. ","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.mantissaBits","kind":"def","line":54,"name":"Float.Model.Format.mantissaBits","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.lean#L54-L56"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.numBits\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">Format</span>.<span class=\"name\">numBits</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The total number of bits in the packed representation. ","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format.numBits","kind":"def","line":50,"name":"Float.